dataLineage.statement:
Layer was downloaded as a shapefile by ITOS from the UNOCHA COD Registry. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. The geometry was updated by cleaning its attributes and topology. The layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
The following errors were found and fixed by ITOS:
1. Removed marginal fields 'LAT' and 'LONG' 2. Created and populated admin 0 name and pcode fields. 3. Created and populated a reference name field. 4. Admin 1 name field changed to proper case from ALL CAPS. 5. Pcodes were fully constructed by adding admin 0 portion ("CO"). 6. Admin 1 names were given special characters to match names in Admin 1 layer. 7. Renamed Admin 1 value for unit ʺCO11001ʺ from ʺCundinamarcaʺ to ʺBogotá D.C.ʺ. 8. Renamed Admin 1 value for unit ʺManaureʺ from ʺLa Guajiraʺ to ʺCesarʺ. 9. 42 units had their Admin 1 names changed from ʺValleʺ to ʺValle del Caucaʺ. 10. Fixed gap and overlap errors in geometry.
